        <h3 class="fc-blue-2">Baffle Box vs Sewn-Through Box…What’s the difference? </h3>
        <p class="mb-2 mb-lg-4 tcs-copy-medium">
            A well-made comforter is constructed to help ensure that warmth is evenly distributed. There are two main types of comforter construction in down comforters—baffle box and sewn-through box.  
            The one you select is a matter of personal preference.</br>
            In a baffle box construction, the stitching that creates the pockets for the down, is separated by internal fabric walls inside the comforter, creating a smooth look from the top.</br>
            In sewn-through box construction, the stitching that creates the pockets for the down, goes through the top and bottom layers of fabric, creating a puffy, pillow-like look from the top. 
        </p>

